It might not be the use case that you want, but you can create a compressed version of the data in a table using an EXTERNAL TABLE statement. E.g. like this

    CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE &#39;supplier.gz&#39;  USING
    (CCSID 1208 s3(
        &#39;s3.amazonaws.com&#39;
    ,   &#39;&lt;S3-access-key-ID&gt;&#39;
    ,   &#39;&lt;S3-secret-access-key&gt;&#39;
        &#39;&lt;my_bucket&gt;&#39;
    ) 
    AS SELECT * FROM supplier

adding the `PARTITION ALL` into the `USING` will get you one file per data slice, which might not be what you want, but the statement will run faster.  You could also use `COMPRESS LZ4` and you will get a LZ4 compressed file (or files) which again will be faster.

